Metadata: Smenochromenes, unusual macrocyclic sesquiterpene hydroquinone derivatives from a Seychelles sponge of the genus "Smenospongia"

Compounds of mixed biogenesis that are based on the farnesyl hydroquinone skeleton are commonly found in Dictyoceratid sponges and occasionally in brown algae of the genus Dictyopteris. Smenochromenes A-D are four unusual macrocyclic chromenes that can be derived by cyclization of farnesyl hydroquinone. The unusual geometry of smenochromene A gives rise to some unexpected spectral data. The sponge "Smenospongia" sp. also contains smenodiol, which is related to compounds previously found in this genus.
